  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat the oven to 180°C. Peel and finely chop the onion and garlic."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Get a large, shallow casserole dish over a medium heat with lots of olive oil, then add the onion. Cook for 10 mins, or until softened. Add the garlic, chilli flakes and cinnamon, then cook for 1 min. Tip in the chopped tomatoes, oregano, water and a big pinch of salt. Bring to the boil. Once the pan is simmering, add the orzo and give everything a stir. Transfer the dish to the oven and cook for 15 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, remove the middle section of shell from the prawns, leaving the heads and tails intact. Devein each one by cutting an incision along the back and removing the trail."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "After the cooking time is complete, remove the dish from the oven and give everything a good stir. Add the prawns and mix again. Crumble the feta over the surface, add a drizzle of olive oil, then bake for 15 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, pick the dill leaves."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To serve, remove the dish from the oven and sprinkle chilli flakes and dill on top. Zest over the lemon, then serve with lemon wedges on the side."
    }
  ],
